The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | US pat for graceful Buddha
                                                                                                               US pat for graceful Buddha
          A STAFF REPORTER                          Roemer at Jorasanko. (Bishwarup Dutta)                                  
	Calcutta, Oct. 13: A day after Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee described Prime Minister Manmohan Singh as an honourable man, he received a gift from the US President  neither would make Prakash Karat happy.        
	US ambassador to India, Timothy Roemer, handed over two books written by Barack Obama to the chief minister when he met him at the Writers Buildings today.        
	I gave him two books, Dreams From My Father and The Audacity of Hope, sent by Barack Obama. He also gave me a gift which I wont reveal to you, said Roemer.        
	During the 75-minute meeting. Roemer and Bhattacharjee exchanged matters of common interest, from international terrorism to US investment in Bengal. The chief minister requested his help in bringing in investment. Roemer wanted to know about Maoist activities in the state.        
	The US envoy described Bhattacharjee as graceful, engaging and a talented politician.        
	When President Obama asked me to take this role, he told me that this relationship between (the) US and India was not only the most important relation but also the best relation we had, said Roemer.        
	The ambassador began his maiden trip to the city with a visit to the Tagores Jorasanko home. He later discussed growth prospects, the help needed and the recent roadblocks with members of the American Chamber of Commerce India.        
	We told him that despite recent events, business fundamentals in Bengal were strong, said Acclaris MD Kalyan Kar. Representatives of over a dozen American companies in the eastern region were present at the meeting.                                                                                                                                                                             
